A social worker and a student were almost hijacked by armed men in Philippi this week. CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape Social Development Department says attacks on social workers cannot be tolerated.A social worker and a student were almost hijacked by armed men in Philippi this week.The pair had visited a disabled woman in the area on Thursday when a group of armed men surrounded their vehicle.The suspects were chased away by residents who had seen them approaching the car.Earlier in June, two social workers were robbed at knifepoint in the same area.The department's Sihle Ngobese said: We sharply condemn any attempted attack or attack on any of our officials in the Western Cape government, especially our social workers. They are our foot soldiers. These are individuals who go beyond the call of duty and often in the poorest communities. 